entry.title: Ukraine Intensifies Strikes Against Russian-Controlled Areas
entry.content: Ukrainian attacks in Donbas came as Moscow unleashed new salvoes of long-range missiles—some of them shot down by air defenses—on cities across the country.

entry.title: Ukraine's Farmers Start Harvest With Few Places to Store Grain
entry.content: Silos and warehouses are holding millions of tons of older grains and seeds, with export routes blocked.

entry.title: Brazilian Police Probe Illegal Fishermen Over Amazon Double Homicide
entry.content: Gunmen targeted indigenous expert Bruno Pereira, investigators said, and then turned weapon on British journalist Dom Phillips, likely to silence him.
